# Founding Member referral program: /join?ref=CODE is the alternate entry
# point alongside /r/CODE (a Cloudflare Pages Function, functions/r/[code].js)
# — both must work per the program spec. Cloudflare Pages preserves the
# query string on a plain redirect, so ?ref=CODE survives onto /login, where
# a small snippet reads it and sets the same scalpclock_ref cookie /r/CODE sets.
/join /login 302

# Any /blog/category/<slug> without its own static HTML file falls back to
# the generic template, which reads the slug from the URL and renders
# whatever posts.json has for that category (or an honest "nothing yet").
# Cloudflare Pages evaluates _redirects wildcard rules BEFORE static-asset
# matching (confirmed via `wrangler pages dev` — the old comment's assumption
# that exact files "still win" was wrong), so real category pages need an
# explicit passthrough rule ABOVE the wildcard or they get caught by it and
# rewritten to _generic.html — which then 308s to its own extensionless URL,
# re-matches this same wildcard, and loops forever. List every real static
# category file here as it's added.
/blog/category/pattern-lessons /blog/category/pattern-lessons 200
/blog/category/scalpclock-tutorials /blog/category/scalpclock-tutorials 200
/blog/category/trading-education /blog/category/trading-education 200
/blog/category/_generic /blog/category/_generic 200
/blog/category/* /blog/category/_generic.html 200
